# DIG Browser: the signature DIG-identity toolbar button + panel (the
# Brave-Shields analogue).
#
# A dedicated toolbar button (the DIG shield mark, dig_shield.icon) sits next to
# the wallet button. Pressing it opens the DIG identity panel — chia://shields —
# anchored just beneath the button, the way Brave anchors its Shields panel under
# the lion. The panel unifies, under one DIG identity: the active page's dig://
# "verified / served-locally" status and the browser's privacy posture
# (ad/tracker/fingerprint controls, DNT, HTTPS-Only, encrypted DNS).
#
# The panel page itself (chia://shields) is an embedded HTML resource served by
# the in-process dig handler — the same crash-safe pattern as chia://about /
# chia://welcome; it is generated by build.py from dig/shields/dig_shields.html
# into dig_shields_html.inc (no patch needed for the generated .inc). The
# chia://shields host dispatch + the chia://privacy settings-rewrite live in
# windows-dig-browser-ux.patch (dig_url_loader_factory.cc / ccbc) and the icon is
# registered in windows-dig-browser-ux.patch (vector_icons/BUILD.gn).
#
# The button reads the ACTIVE tab's dig status at press time (via the
# DigTabHelper + the committed URL) and passes it to the panel as query params,
# so the panel reflects the page it opened over.
